  "title": "Ecommerce Warehouse Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Our company fosters a dynamic and friendly environment where everyone knows each other and work together towards a common goal. We prioritize teamwork, open communication and mutal support. Be part of our team where every voice matters and every contribution counts.</p><p><p>- Process and print online orders from e-commerce platforms</p></p><p><p>- Pick, pack, and prepare orders accurately for dispatch</p></p><p><p>- Handle inbound and outbound goods, including stock receiving and checking</p></p><p><p>- Plan and optimize delivery routes using navigation and logistics apps</p></p><p><p>- Coordinate with drivers or delivery partners to ensure timely deliveries</p></p><p><p>- Manage returns and exchanges from online platforms</p></p><p><p>- Update order status and inventory records as required</p></p><p><p>- Ensure packing standards and quality control are met</p></p><p><p>- Support daily warehouse and e-commerce operations</p></p><p><p>- Maintain a clean and organized work area</p></p><p><p>- Work closely with team members to meet operational deadlines</p></p><p><p>- Be agile, adaptable, and able to multitask in a fast-paced environment</p></p><p><strong>Locations:</strong></p><ul><li>87 Defu Lane 10 (5.5 days work week Mon - Fri 9 - 6pm, Sat 9-2pm)</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><p>- Annual leave</p><p>- Birthday leave</p><p>- Performance Bonus</p>",
